data.title: Caesar and Cleopatra
data.meta_description: Caesar and Cleopatra (1946) starring Claude Rains, Vivien Leigh, Stewart Granger and directed by Gabriel Pascal.
data.text: Cleopatra (Vivien Leigh) hasn't been on the throne of the Pharaohs of Egypt very long when Julius Caesar (Claude Rains) pays a visit. Caesar finds the prospect of romance more tempting than he expected, since Cleopatra is a rare woman who is bright as well as beautiful. And for Cleopatra, a friendly relationship with the most powerful man in the world may pay dividends in the future.
